<p>On Monday we held the first Leeds gov design meet at <a href="https://odileeds.org">ODI Leeds</a>. 26 people turned up. Thank you for coming!</p>

<p>And a massive thank you to the four people who led the sessions:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://twitter.com/twoshedz">Pete Smith</a>, from NHS Digital, on <em>Simple improvements to patient referral letters</em></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://twitter.com/Ellayanor">Ellie Craven</a>, from GDS, on <em>When free text is the enemy of data quality</em></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://twitter.com/designandpolicy">James Johnson</a>, from DWP, on <em>Solving complex policy problems using design tools and techniques</em></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://twitter.com/cjforms">Caroline Jarrett</a>, from Effortmark, <em>reviewing a form</em> with everyone in the room</p>
  </li>
</ul>

